Arp (address resolution protocol)
--------------------------------- 

Map an IP address -> MAC address

 Why arp is Needed?
 In a network:
   • Devices communicate using IP addresses (logical)
   • But actual data transfer happens using MAC addresses (physical)

 How arp works?
  • Your system wants to send data to 192.168.1.1
  • It checks arp cache
  • If not found -> sends ARP Request (broadcast)
  • Target device replies with ARP reply (unicast)
  • Mapping stored in ARP table

  # Hands-on commands
    View ARP table: arp -a
    Modern alternative: ip neigh

Real World Scenarios
--------------------

> Scenario 1: First Communication in Network
  * Device doesn’t know MAC
  * Uses ARP to find it

> Scenario 2: Duplicate IP issue
  * Same IP mapped to multiple MACs (network conflict)

